aiHeadline: Trade Wars Escalate: U.S. Agriculture Faces Export Declines and Rising Costs
aiBlurb: In March 2025, escalating trade tensions led to significant impacts on U.S. agriculture. New tariffs and retaliatory measures resulted in a sharp decline in soybean exports to China and increased fertilizer costs for American farmers.
